antalistvan:
Same issue here... After a "Clear Cache" or after any Category modification on the Admin pages, the site can stuck in an unresponsive state for minutes, using an F8 size VM in Azure. Something need to do with it.
. Currently, we are trying to workaround the ClearKeys issue.
We made the following changes in the MemoryCacheManager.cs:
Added a new class property, contains only those keys are marked to delete:
protected static readonly ConcurrentDictionary<string, bool> _keysToRemove;
In the CTOR we initialized that
_keysToRemove = new ConcurrentDictionary<string, bool>();
Changed the TryRemoveKey's inner content to this:
_keysToRemove.TryRemove(key, out _);
            if (!_allKeys.TryRemove(key, out _))
            {
                if (_allKeys.TryUpdate(key, false, true))
                {
                    _keysToRemove.TryAdd(key, true);
                }
            }
And finally, replaced the ClearKeys to this:
foreach (var key in _keysToRemove.Keys.ToList())
            {
                TryRemoveKey(key);
            }
We are testing this modification in our production environment, and after an hour, we experienced that the overall site performance is much better than anytime before.
It's not 20% or 50%. It's about 2-3x faster than before.
For example a simple ajax call went down from about 500ms to 100-130ms.
I'm not sure this is a correct workaround or not, because I don't know the full impact of the changes to the nopCommerce.
I think some redesing/refact is needed here from nopCommerce.. Just another proof.. From the picture, is clearly seeable the modification make the site performs better.

